n: A Precedent of Dubious Relevance]\n* [https://app.curiositystream.com/video/1252 Afghanistan 1979: The War That Changed the World, Icarus Films], featuring interviews with numerous U.S. and Soviet officials including Gorbachev\n\n{{Soviet-Afghan War}}\n{{USSR conflicts}}\n{{Russian Conflicts}}\n{{Cold War}}\n{{Soviet occupation}}\n{{Brezhnev era}}\n{{Fall of Communism}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Soviet War In Afghanistan}}\n [[Category:Soviet\u2013Afghan War|01]]\n[[Category:Afghanistan conflict (1978\u2013present)]]\n[[Category:Cold War conflicts]]\n[[Category:1979 in Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:1980s in Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1979]]\n[[Category:1980s conflicts]]\n[[Category:Invasions of Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Invasions by the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Soviet military occupations]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Anti-communism in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the Soviet Union|Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Guerrilla warfare]]\n[[Category:Proxy wars]]\n[[Category:Cold War military history of the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Soviet chemical weapons program]]\n[[Category:Anti-communism in Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Communism in Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Islamism in Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:1979 in the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:1980s in the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Afghanistan\u2013Soviet Union relations]]\n[[Category:History of Islam in Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Terrorism in Pakistan]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-semi-indef}}\n{{short description|War between the Soviet Union and Afghan insurgents, 1979\u201389}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2012}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n|conflict    = Soviet\u2013Afghan War\n|partof      = the [[Cold War]] and the continuous [[Afghanistan conflict (1978\u2013present)|Afghanistan conflict]]\n|image       = [[File:Mortar attack on Shigal Tarna garrison, Kunar Province, 87.jpg|border|300px]]\n|caption     = Mujahideen fighters in the [[